# Arcades Profile — Cursor Rules

## Tech stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript (strict)
- Payload CMS v3 with PostgreSQL
- Tailwind CSS + SASS
- Vercel deployment

## Package manager
Always use **npm**. Never suggest `yarn`, `pnpm`, or `bun`.

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode — no `any` unless absolutely necessary
- Prefer functional components and React hooks
- Co-locate types with the files that use them
- Use Tailwind utility classes; avoid inline styles

## Project conventions
- App Router pages and API routes live in `app/`
- Payload collections are defined in `collections/` and registered in `payload.config.ts`
- Shared utilities belong in `lib/`
- All new API routes go under `app/api/`

## Commands
- `npm run dev` — start dev server (port 3000)
- `npm run lint` — ESLint
- `npm test` — run tests with tsx
- `npm run build` — production build

## Environment
- Required vars are in `.env.example` — never commit real secrets
- `MCP_API_KEY` and `PAYLOAD_API_KEY` are separate — rotate independently
